DiAdjList, UAdjList
 class AdjList
extends FilterGraph
implements Graph

Simple adjacency list implementation of the Digraph interface. This class is primarily intended for use with programmer-supplied Node and Edge classes, giving an easy way to use many of the supplied algorithms with arbitrary application-specific graphical data structures.

Constructor Detail

AdjList

public AdjList(Node[] nodes)
Construct an adjacency list from a set of nodes in the array nodes.

It is assumed that the nodes have ids which are equal to the index in the array nodes. Neither the array nor the contained nodes are copied to produce the graph.

Parameters:
nodes - the nodes to be vertices in the resulting graph.

AdjList

public AdjList(Node[] nodes,
               int numEdges)
Construct an adjacency list graph from a set of nodes, with an explicit declaration of the number of edges.

If numEdges is incorrecct, subsequent calls to edgeSize() will give misinformation, leading to various problems including edge attribute arrays of incorrect size.

Parameters:
nodes - the nodes in the graph.
numEdges - the total number of edges in the graph.

toString

public java.lang.String toString()
Produces a string for the graph in a simple adjacency list representation. Each node n is listed in order (by Node.nodeId()), followed by a colon ':' and a space separated list of the nodes to which n is linked by an edge.
